# Connectivity Test Results

To verify end-to-end connectivity, ping tests were performed from **PC2 (Windows — 192.168.10.10)** to multiple devices across the network.

The tests confirmed successful communication across **VLANs, routing boundaries, and the OSPF WAN link**.  
Inter-VLAN routing using **Router-on-a-Stick on R1** was verified by reaching the **192.168.30.0/24 network** from the **192.168.10.0/24 segment**.  

OSPF route propagation was also validated. Devices on R1's local network were able to reach **R2’s WAN and LAN interfaces**.

During testing, **Windows Firewall was configured to allow ICMP Echo requests** so PC2 could respond to ping traffic.

